issues.title: Wrong structure on `let b = 1 = 1 in` (OCaml)
issues.body:
plugin version: 0.111-2023.1

### Description

This code is parsed into the wrong structure:

```ocaml
let f () =
  let b : bool = 1 = 1 in
  let x = 0 in
  x
```

- test.ml
  - f
    - b
  - x
comments:
However, parentheses fix it:

```ocaml
let f () =
  let b : bool = (1 = 1) in
  let x = 0 in
  x
```

- test.ml
  - f
    - b
    - x

It looks like the fix doesn't support general expressions, e.g.:

```ocaml
let f () =
  let b : bool = ignore () = () in
  let x = 0 in
  x
```

- test.ml
  - f
    - b
  - x

Thank you for all the other fixes; that was fast!

It works on the previous example, but not on this one:

```ocaml
let f () =
  let b : bool = ignore "" = () in
  let x = 0 in
  x
```

issues.title: Structure panel shows "Unknown presentation ..." for "module X : sig ..."
issues.body:
plugin version: 0.117-2023.1

### Description

The structure panel should show the appropriate info instead of the "Unknown presentation" error message.  I suspect this is a regression--I think I would have noticed this long ago.

![image](https://github.com/giraud/reasonml-idea-plugin/assets/1253341/8a07b8d4-bfa8-4313-99eb-ffc2210166d3)


```
module X : sig
  type t =
    | A
    | B
end
```
